# Site Template Conventions

## Config schema (`site.config.json`)

Required top-level keys: `meta`, `brand`, `theme`, `hero`, `about`, `services`, `portfolio`, `testimonial`, `booking`, `contact`, `social`, `footer`.

| Section | Shape |
|---------|-------|
| `meta` | `{ title, description }` |
| `brand` | `{ name, tagline }` |
| `theme.colors` | `{ ivory, blush, plum, gold, charcoal, rose }` — hex strings |
| `hero` | `{ eyebrow, headline, headlineEmphasis, headlineSuffix, lede, ctaPrimary, ctaSecondary, image }` |
| `about` | `{ eyebrow, heading, paragraphs[], image }` |
| `services` | `{ eyebrow, heading, items[] }` — each item: `{ title, price, description }` |
| `portfolio` | `{ eyebrow, heading, note, items[] }` — each item: `{ label, image? }` |
| `testimonial` | `{ quote, cite }` |
| `booking` | `{ heading, text, calendlyUrl, ctaLabel }` |
| `contact` | `{ email, phone, location }` |
| `social` | `{ instagram, pinterest, tiktok }` — empty string if unknown |
| `footer` | `{ copyrightYear, locationBlurb }` |

Use `site.config.example.json` as the reference when adding fields.

## Rules

- Client content lives in config only — never hardcode in `templates/index.html`
- CSS variable names are stable: `--ivory`, `--blush`, `--plum`, `--gold`, `--charcoal`, `--rose`, `--line`
- Images: WebP or JPG in `assets/`; hero ~800×1000, portfolio ~600×690
- Image paths in config: `hero.jpg` or `assets/hero.jpg`; empty string uses gradient placeholder
- Service `price` may include HTML (e.g. `/ person` span); `description` is plain text (escaped at build)
- One page, anchor nav — no routes or frameworks unless explicitly requested
- Build copies `assets/` → `dist/assets/`; output is always `dist/index.html`

## Build

```bash
npm run build
```

After config or asset changes, always rebuild and verify before reporting success.
